The '''Ambewela Aitken Spence Wind Farm''' is small [[wind farm]] in [[Ambewela]], owned and operated by Ace Wind Power, a subsidiary of [[Aitken Spence]]. As of October 2012, it is one of the only few operating multi-megawatt wind farms in [[Sri Lanka]]. The wind farm consists of {{Nowrap|12 [[wind turbines]]}} of {{Nowrap|250 [[Kilowatt|KW]]}} each, totalling the plant installed capacity to {{Nowrap|3 [[megawatts]]}}.<ref name=DailyNews1>{{cite web|title=Blue chips eye more hydro, wind power plants |url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2011/06/08/bus05.asp |publisher=DailyNews.lk |accessdate=7 October 2012 |date=8 June 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110823125438/http://www.dailynews.lk/2011/06/08/bus05.asp |archivedate=23 August 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Aitken Spence PBT Grows by 25% in First Quarter|url=http://www.aitkenspence.com/media_centre/latest_news_full_story.asp?NewsId=1350|accessdate=7 October 2012|date=4 August 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140403152249/http://aitkenspence.com/media_centre/latest_news_full_story.asp?NewsId=1350|archive-date=2014-04-03|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
