{{unreferenced|date=November 2014}}
The '''minor tetra''' (''Hyphessobrycon minor'') is a small fish from the [[Essequibo River]] in [[Guyana]] in South America, closely resembling its relative, the [[serpae tetra]], from the [[Amazon basin|Amazon]] and [[Paraguay Basin|Paraguay]]. These two very similar species are separated geographically, so they would not interbreed.

