{{italic title}} '''''Mountaintop Removal''''' is a 2007 [[documentary film]] directed by Michael O'Connell. The film explores how [[mountaintop removal mining]] in [[West Virginia]] has affected local communities. Filmed over a two-year period, ''Mountain Top Removal'' features community advocates, such as Ed Wiley, [[Larry Gibson]], [[Julia Bonds]], [[Maria Gunnoe]], and Mountain Justice Summer volunteers, in their efforts to oppose the destruction of Southern [[Appalachia]]'s natural landscape. The film includes commentary from [[Jeff Goodell]], author of ''[[Big Coal: The Dirty Secret Behind America's Energy Future]]'', geologists Dr. William Schlesinger and Dr. Peter Taft, and also Bill Raney, President of the [[West Virginia Coal Association]].<ref>[http://www.athensfest.org/?film=MountainTopRemoval Mountain Top Removal]</ref><ref>[http://www.indyweek.com/gyrobase/Content?oid=oid%3A261063 Michael O'Connell's Mountain Top Removal raised awareness of coal mining practices]</ref> The film won the ''Reel Current Award'' (presented by [[Al Gore]]) at the 2008 [[Nashville Film Festival]].<ref>[http://www.nashvillefilmfestival.org/NaFF/Archives/2008AwardWinners/tabid/358/Default.aspx 2008 Nashville Film Festival Award Winners]</ref> ''Mountaintop Removal'' also received a Jury award at the 2008 Wild and Scenic Film Festival, Audience award at the 2008 [[Woods Hole Film Festival]] and was screened at [[Lincoln Center for the Performing Arts|The Lincoln Center]] on [[Earth Day]] April 22, 2008.<ref name="Haw River Films">{{cite web|url=http://www.hawriverfilms.com/id11.html|title=Mountain Top Removal documentary|publisher=Haw River Films|accessdate=5 January 2014}}</ref> The film is currently being distributed nationwide on [[PBS]] through NETA. The film's soundtrack includes music by [[Jim Lauderdale]], [[Donna the Buffalo]], John Specker and [[Sarah Hawker]].
