'''Richard McCarthy''' is the co-founder of the [[Crescent City Farmers Market]]<ref>http://dinersjournal.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/01/08/new-leader-for-slow-food-usa/</ref> and the executive director of [[Slow Food USA]].<ref>http://www.slowfoodusa.org/index.php/about_us/details/staff_bios/ Slow Food USA Staff Bios</ref>  He was the founder of Market Umbrella and the Farmers Market Coalition.  In 2012, he was named a "Hero of the New South" by [[Southern Living]] magazine.<ref>http://www.southernliving.com/travel/1203-heroes-mccarthy-00417000077368/ Southern Living Magazine</ref>  He is a graduate of the [[London School of Economics]]. A small selection of McCarthy's personal papers are archived at [[Loyola University New Orleans]].<ref>{{cite web |title=New Orleans Social Justice and Activism 1980s-1990s Collection Finding Aid |url=http://library.loyno.edu/assets/handouts/archives/Collection%2044%20NOSJ.pdf |website=Special Collections & Archives, Loyola University New Orleans, J. Edgar & Louise S. Monroe Library}}</ref>

